Dialogue: A powerful ring, indeed.  Do you no longer wish to keep it? I can offer you 16,000 gold in exchange for it.
A powerful ring, indeed.  Do you no longer wish to keep it? If you wish to sell it, I'm prepared to offer you 16,000 gold for it.
A wonderful shield, and very resistant to magicka, from what I understand.  May we add this to our collection? I can offer you 30,000 gold in exchange for it.
Ah, Phynaster's Ring.  I trust it has served you as well as it served him all those years ago.  Are you interested in selling it to the Museum? I can offer you 9,000 gold for it.

Ah, Phynaster's Ring.  I trust it has served you as well as it served him all those years ago.  Are you interested in selling it to the Museum? Or perhaps donating it? I can offer you 9,000 gold if you choose to sell it.

Ah, the Ice Blade.  Often have I heard tales of it...  one wonders what might have become of it, had the assassination succeeded.  Well, no matter.  Do you wish to sell it? I'm prepared to offer you 30,000 gold for it.

Ah, the Ice Blade.  Often have I heard tales of it...  one wonders what might have become of it, had the assassination succeeded.  Well, no matter.  Do you wish to sell it? Or maybe donate it? I can offer you 30,000 gold if you choose to sell.
Ah, the very definition of an artifact.  They don't make them like this anymore, eh?  So, are you willing to part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold for it.
Ah, the very definition of an artifact.  They don't make them like this anymore, eh?  So, will you sell it?  I can offer you 30,000 gold for it.
Ah, yes.  The blade forged from a dragon fang, surpassed in its wonder only by its difficulty to pronounce.  Do you wish to sell this to the museum? I can offer you 16,000 gold for it.

Ah, yes.  The blade forged from a dragon fang, surpassed in its wonder only by its difficulty to pronounce.  Do you wish to sell this to the museum? Or perhaps donate it? I can offer you 16,000 gold if you choose to sell it.
Ahh... Hircine's Hide.  What a prize!  Are you willing to part with it? I can offer you 30
Another shield for our fine collection.  Are you willing to sell it? I can offer 13,500 gold for it.
As you wish. Be careful you are not accidentally struck with it, lest we be unable to hold a conversation in the future.
As you wish.
Auriel's Bow... interesting.  Is that ash yams I smell? I can offer you 15,000 gold, if you wish.
Bring me a couple quality pieces, and I'll be able to help you, friend.
Created for evil purposes or not, the ring still has a place in our collection.  Thank you.
Disappointing, but understandable.  Let me know if you reconsider.
Do take good care of it, then.  That staff is one of the most prized artifacts in all of Tamriel.
Do with it what you will.  It is yours to use, for good or for evil.
Excellent.  Small though it is, it shall hold a prominent place in our collection.
Excellent.  This will make a wonderful addition to our collection.
Greetings.  I am Torasa Aram, Curator of the Mournhold Museum of Artifacts.
Hilbongard's masterpiece, the Skull Crusher.  I am impressed.  This is quite a find.  Do you wish to turn it over to the museum? I can offer you 24,000 gold for it.
Hilbongard's masterpiece, the Skull Crusher.  I am impressed.  This is quite a find.  Do you wish to turn it over to the museum? If you wish to sell it, I can offer you 24,000 gold in exchange.
How is it that you have this?  It belongs to the Museum! GUARDS!!!
How is it that you have this?  This belongs to the museum!  GUARDS!!!
I am truly honored. Thank you.
I certainly understand.  It is perhaps more valuable when used than when sitting here in a display case.

I do not wish to know what you must have been through to acquire this ring.  If it has outlived its usefulness to you, perhaps you would be willing to sell it to the museum? If so, I can give you 11,000 gold in exchange.

I do not wish to know what you must have been through to acquire this ring.  If it has outlived its usefulness to you, perhaps you would be willing to sell it to the museum? Or perhaps you would like to donate it? I can offer you 11,000 gold, should you decide to sell it.

I don't even have it on display, because I haven't been able to positively identify it yet. It's a shield of Dwemer make, but not traditional in any sense of the word. The pieces of it just don't seem to match, and I've wondered if it isn't some sort of a fake. I suppose I might be able to part with it, but I'll need some compensation.
I hope they are content to be here in the museum, rather than running through Morrowind's countryside. Thank you.
I must admit, I am only vaguely familiar with this piece.  I shall have to do a bit more research on it.  Would you be willing to sell it? I can offer you 30,000 if you choose to sell it.

I must admit, I am only vaguely familiar with this piece.  I shall have to do a bit more research on it.  Would you be willing to sell it? Or perhaps donate it? I can offer you 30,000 if you choose to sell it.
I personally don't believe the rumors that the blade chooses who wields it, and I think it will be quite safe here in our display case.  Thank you.
I understand that you've found this thing of legend and brought it to the goddess.
I understand, though I'm disappointed. It's a piece of such local historical significance.
I wonder whether or not the stories are true.  Is the soul of Hasedoki really contained in this staff?  Either way, are you prepared to part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold for it.

I wonder whether or not the stories are true.  Is the soul of Hasedoki really contained in this staff?  Either way, are you prepared to part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold, if you choose to sell it.
I'd heard of the Ebony Mail, but never seen it.  It would fit well in our collection; will you part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold for it.
If Hasedoki's life-force is indeed contained within this staff, I hope it is content to remain here in the museum.  Thank you.
If you should change your mind, please let me know.

I'm always looking for new pieces for the Museum of Artifacts. Unique items, armor and weapons of lore--you know the stuff. If you would be willing to donate a couple to the Museum, I'd be willing to part with the shield.
I'm sorry to hear that.  Perhaps you'll change your mind.
I'm sorry you feel that way.
I'm very proud to have this remarkable piece for our collection.  Thank you.

Incredible.  So little is known about the Spear, I'm at a loss for words.  They say it was used in the fall of the Battlespire, you know... Do you wish to sell it to the museum? I can offer you 30,000 gold for it.

Information is scarce at best when it comes to this artifact. Some have said it was pulled from a lich when it was defeated; others say it was developed by an evil mage who wanted the power of a lich without the.... drawbacks. Either way, it is a powerful item indeed. Do you wish to part with it? I can offer you 11,000 gold for it.

Intriguing. I've never seen a sword like this. And you say you got it where? Hmm. Well, it's certainly worthy of the museum's attention. Do you wish to part with it? I can give you 30,000 gold for it.

Intriguing. I've never seen a sword like this. And you say you got it where? Hmm. Well, it's certainly worthy of the museum's attention. Do you wish to part with it? If so, I can give you 30,000 gold, should you decide to sell it.
It is your choice, of course.  Please let me know if you wish to reconsider your decision.
It will occupy a place of honor in our collection.  Thank you.
It's a remarkable item to add to our collection.  Thank you.
It's been quite popular with the tourists.
It's interesting to see that something most people find so offensive is one of the biggest draws at the museum.  Wouldn't you say?
It's your choice, of course.
It's your choice, of course.
It's your choice, of course.  I'd suggest exercising judgment in using it, however.  Necromancy is a dangerous thing.
It's your choice.  I hope you find it useful.
It's your choice. I'd be cautious with it, were I you.

Legend has it that a nobleman sank his fortune into creating a blade of supreme power. Two smiths on opposite ends of Tamriel created each half of the blade, unaware of the other, with the hope that no one man, save the owner of the blade, would know its true power. Unfortunately, the smiths were not given enough instruction, and created halves with enchantments that completely negated each other. Do you wish to part with it? I can offer you 20,000 for it.
Quite a weapon, isn't it?  I'd be honored to add it to our collection.  Is that your wish? I can offer you 15,000 gold in exchange for it.
Quite a weapon, isn't it?  I'd be honored to add it to our collection.  Is that your wish? If you choose to sell it, I can offer you 15,000 gold in exchange for it.
Quite an addition for our collection.  It is one of the oldest artifacts in all of Tamriel, to my knowledge.  Thank you.
Remarkable boots... what the wind must feel like while running in them! Do you wish to part with them? I can offer you 30,000 gold for them.
Remarkable boots... what the wind must feel like while running in them! Do you wish to part with them? I can offer you 30,000 gold in exchange for them.

Rumor has it the God of Justice himself wielded this hammer. I am inclined to believe it, as none less than a god could ever hope to raise the thing, let alone swing it. It took four men just to lift it onto the podium for display...
Said to have been left behind by the Worm King himself.  Evil, but beautiful. If you wish to sell it, I can give you 17,000 gold for it.
Simply beautiful.  Are you willing to part with it? I can offer you 17
So be it.  Should you change your mind, you know where to find me.
Splendid. I must say I feel more comfortable with this in the Museum's collection than I would knowing it was somewhere out in the world.
Thank you for allowing us to add it to the collection.
Thank you for allowing us to add them to our collection.
Thank you so much.  This should be adequate payment.
Thank you so much.  This will be a wonderful addition to the Museum.
Thank you.
Thank you.
Thank you.
Thank you.  A wonderful addition indeed.
Thank you.  We shall display it proudly.
Thank you.  You are a true friend of the museum.
Thank you. It will be safe here, I assure you.
Thank you. It will take up a, err, special place in our museum. Somewhere upstairs, perhaps. Somewhere dark, as well.
Thank you. It's rare to find an item for our collection with such a distinctive aroma.
Thank you. Perhaps now that it will reside here, we'll have an opportunity to study it and learn more about it.
Thank you. They'll certainly be one of our more amusing artifacts, I'm sure.
Thank you.  I assure you it will be well cared for.
Thank you.  This will take a prominent place in our collection, as I'm sure it will be very popular for our visitors.
The ceremonial dagger of General Symmachus? How did you come to possess this? What a local treasure! If you're willing to part with it, I can offer you 10,000 gold for it.
The decision is yours. Though I will advise caution if you intend to make use of the robe.

The Mazed Band may actually be no more than a legend, though there is no doubt of Barilzar's existence, or his power. It has been said that the Mazed Band was able to open rifts in time and space...that it could even open the gates of Oblivion. It's been said that it would take one of divine birth to wield the ring. Some speculate that that was how Barilzar himself met his end. Of course, this is all conjecture. No one really knows what happened to the man or the Band. All of that was lost centuries ago.
The Museum has been compensated quite well. Thank you for your donations.

The Museum is always interested in expanding its collection; do you wish to sell something?  I must advise you, however, that all transactions are final.  This is not a pawn shop; you may not come back and reclaim artifacts when you feel like it. I can tell you that the Museum is prepared to offer fifty percent of the value of any artifact, up to 30,000 gold; I believe you'll find this is a more profitable offer than any other that will be made to you.

The museum is interested in purchasing unique artifacts from all over Morrowind. If you have anything we might have an interest in, we can discuss the specifics. I can tell you up front that the Museum is willing to offer half the total value of any artifact sold, up to 30,000 gold. We do have a limited budget, you see.

The Museum is privately funded, and is an effort to collect and display many of the artifacts from this part of the world.  Should you want to sell something you feel the Museum will be interested in, bring the item here and we can assess its value.  Be warned, however, that theft is a serious matter, and likely to equal a death warrant for any foolish enough to attempt it.

The pieces of the Blade of Nerevar here in Mournhold? Now there's something I'd like to get my hands on for the Museum. I can't say that I have seen any that I know of, but I do have one piece from roughly the same time, and it seems to be of Dwemer construction.
The Staff of Magnus.  Quite a prize, indeed.  Are you willing to part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold in exchange for it.
This will make a wonderful addition to our collection, I'm sure.
Unless Syrabane himself comes to collect the ring, it will retain a place in our collection for a long time to come.  Thank you.
Very well.  But do keep an eye on it -- they say the blade passes from owner to owner of its own accord.
Very well. Please don't wear them out - they're too valuable for that.
Very well.  May the staff continue to protect you from the ravages of magicka.
Very well.  May your arrows fly straight and true.
Very well. I doubt any amount of money can adequately compensate for the loss of such a weapon, but here you go.
Very well. It will take up a place in our collection. Likely a place towards the back. Thank you.
Very well. Take good care of it.
Very well. You are a true friend of the museum, to offer such an artifact while expecting nothing in return.
Very well; it's your choice.
We appreciate the chance to display it.  Thank you again.
Welcome back to the Museum.  Are you here to look, or did you wish to sell something?
Well, I don't know what else to call it. You should probably have a smith look at it, though.
Well, please do take care of it, then.  I'd hate to see something happen to such a valuable weapon.
Well, that's your choice. The museum will survive without them.
Well, they're certainly... interesting, aren't they? An odd combination of enchantments, to be sure. Do you wish to sell them to the museum? It's not much, but I can offer you 250 gold for them.
Well, this is a piece I never thought I'd see.  Did you know that the assassin Dram was said to have wielded this bow?  I would be honored to have this on display. I can offer you 21,000 gold for it.
Well, this is quite a find. Do you wish to part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold if you choose to sell it.
Well, well.  The Paladin's Blade.  A wonderful find, to be sure.  Do you wish to part with it? I can offer you 30,000 gold for it.
What a wonderful shield that is!  Are you interested in selling it to the museum? I can offer you 30
What a wonderful shield that is!  Are you interested in selling it to the museum? Or perhaps donating it? I can offer 30
What an incredible weapon.  Are you sure you wish to part with it? I can offer you 30
What an incredible weapon.  Are you sure you wish to part with it? I'm prepared to offer you 30
What?  How is it that you have this?  This was part of the museum's collection!  GUARDS!
What?  How is it that you have this?  This was part of the museum's collection!  GUARDS!
What?  How is it that you have this?  This was part of the museum's collection!  GUARDS!
What? How is it that you have these? They belong to the museum now! GUARDS!
What? How is it that you have this! It's part of the museum's collection! GUARDS!
What? How is it that you have this? It belongs to the museum! GUARDS!
What? How is it that you have this? It belongs to the museum! GUARDS!
What? How is it that you have this? This belongs to the Museum! GUARDS!
What? How is it that you have this? This is part of the museum's collection! GUARDS!
What? How is it you have the Dagger again? It belongs to the Museum now! GUARDS!!!
What? How is that you have these? They were part of the museum's collection! GUARDS!
While I admit I find it repulsive, it's an intriguing piece for our collection.  Thank you.

Worn by Tiber Septim; supposedly a gift to Talos Stormcrown from the Greybeards. Wonderous. Simply wonderous. And you're willing to sell them to the museum? Well, then I can offer you 27,500 gold as compensation.
Yes, it is a wonderful addition to our collection. Thank you again.

Yes, it's a rather...odd piece. From what I've gathered, it was crafted near the end of the Second Age by Kyanka, a slightly deranged Altmer weaponsmith and enchanter. He had a rather warped sense of humor, and apparently delighted at the thought of reducing opponents to a gibbering mess before crushing them to death. The mace has, admittedly, seen little use. Do you wish to part with it? I can offer you 10000 gold for it.
Yes, it's quite an...interesting... piece. I'm glad that it's on display.
Yes, thank you for allowing us to add it to our collection.
Yes, thank you for allowing us to add it to our collection.
Yes, thank you for allowing us to add it to our collection.
Yes, thank you for allowing us to add them to the museum's collection.
Yes, we do thank you for selling it to the Museum.
Yes, we're very honored to have it as part of our collection.
You do not have the blade with you? Return with it, and we can settle the matter.
You don't have Auriel's Bow with you? Then come back with it, and we'll settle the deal.

You don't have the Mace of Slurring with you? Well, bring it in and we can settle the deal.

You don't have the Robe of the Lich with you? Then come back with it, and we'll settle the deal.

You don't have Warlock's Ring with you? Then come back with it, and we'll settle the deal.
You have nerve, I must say. But you must be crazy if you think I'll buy artifacts from you that you've stolen from me.
Your choice.  I take it you have an aversion to poison and lightning?  Not surprising at all.  I hope the ring serves you well.
You're quite sure about that?  Ah, well.  Perhaps at a later date we can discuss it again.
You're quite sure, are you? Very well. Somehow, I think we will get by without it.

You've already been quite a friend to the Museum. I'll give you the piece. I'm classifying it as a Dwemer Battle Shield. As I said, I'm not sure what to make of it. The spike attached to the front of the shield seems to be loose, but a competent smith can probably take care of that for you. Good luck to you, and if you're able to recreate the Blade of Nerevar, I'd love to see the finished product.
What?  How is it that you have this?  This was part of the museum's collection!  GUARDS!
